I"C<p>You need to discuss the following with your manager:</p>

<ol>
  <li><a href="https://www.sachinrekhi.com/product-management-career-ladders-at-8-top-technology-firms">Org ladder</a> - where you stand in the org.</li>
  <li><a href="https://snowflake.medium.com/#1,2,3,2,4,1,1,4,3,2,0,4,2,2,3,0,Cersei%20Lannister,Senior%20Group%20Lead">GFW skill</a> - rating across various tracks relevant for a PM.</li>
  <li><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1FcX7lIZT0db-JvFdW0cUakcDXs_ESuR1haButgj72FA/edit?usp=sharing">Individual development plan</a> - plan for development, closing skill gaps.</li>
  <li><a href="https://support.reflektive.com/hc/en-us/articles/360000578686-Preparing-for-a-Review">360* review</a> - done yearly/biyearly.</li>
  <li><a href="https://manassaloi.com/2020/01/28/one-on-ones.html">1-1 document</a> - for weekly 1-1.</li>
  <li><a href="https://jvns.ca/blog/brag-documents/">Brag doc</a> - to help in promotion.</li>
  <li><a href="https://medium.com/@ianmcall/mind-the-gap-analysis-and-get-promoted-e4bb4462ef40">Gap analysis</a> - close the skill gap and level up with your IDP plan.</li>
  <li><a href="https://manassaloi.com/2020/02/27/kind-of-PM.html">Your USP</a> - what kind of PM do you want yourself to be known as?</li>
  <li><a href="https://medium.com/know-your-team-blog/skip-level-meetings-what-they-are-and-exactly-how-to-run-them-d9c24e63130b">Skip-level 1:1s</a> - Do these.</li>
</ol>

